ul.li:
The _params_ object is unobservable. Its purpose in the algorithm is to ensure that properties of the _options_ object are only accessed once and that the _options_ object can be frozen. Local variables can be used instead, for instance:

  let pin = 2;
  if (options !== undefined) {
      if ("pin" in options) {
          pin = options.pin;
          if ((pin < 0) || (3 < pin))
              throw new RangeError(`invalid pin ${pin}`);
      }
  }
